   CHINA, APR 21-26, 2004},
Organization = {Int Soc Hort Sci; UN, Food \& Agr Org},
Abstract = {`Pingdingshan No. 4', a cross between `791' as the female plant and
   `Hanzhong' winter fragrant-flowered Chinese garlic as the male plant, is
   a new variety of fragrant-flowered garlic cultivated at our institute
   through sexual hybridization by way of continuous multi-generation
   directional selection and mixed pollination. Comparison among various
   varieties, experiments in different regions and example cultivation
   prove that this new variety has many outstanding characteristics, such
   as: short dormant period, strong ability of low temperature resistance
   and disease resistance, fast and vigorous growth, high productivity,
   better appearance, better internal quality, high nutritive value,
   delicious taste, storage and transportation endurance and better
   economic interest. `Pingdingshan No. 4' is a excellent variety and fits
   for growing in open field or greenhouse in all parts of the country.},
